.TH "aa_audit_file" 9 "aa_audit_file" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
aa_audit_file \- handle the auditing of file operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" aa_audit_file
.BI "(struct aa_profile *profile "  ","
.BI "struct aa_perms *perms "  ","
.BI "const char *op "  ","
.BI "u32 request "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "const char *target "  ","
.BI "struct aa_label *tlabel "  ","
.BI "kuid_t ouid "  ","
.BI "const char *info "  ","
.BI "int error "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "profile" 12
the profile being enforced  (NOT NULL)
.IP "perms" 12
the permissions computed for the request (NOT NULL)
.IP "op" 12
operation being mediated
.IP "request" 12
permissions requested
.IP "name" 12
name of object being mediated (MAYBE NULL)
.IP "target" 12
name of target (MAYBE NULL)
.IP "tlabel" 12
target label (MAY BE NULL)
.IP "ouid" 12
object uid
.IP "info" 12
extra information message (MAYBE NULL)
.IP "error" 12
0 if operation allowed else failure error code
.SH "RETURN"
0 or error on failure
